  {
    "id": "bank-a-q146",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "computer-architecture",
    "subtopic": "control-unit",
    "stem": "In the CPU, what is the functionality of the control unit?",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "To decode program instruction",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "To perform logic operations",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "To store program instruction",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "To transfer data to primary storage",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "The control unit fetches instructions and decodes them, then issues the control signals that sequence the rest of the CPU. Logic operations are the ALU's job (B) and storage is memory's (C), which is the usual mix-up.",
    "source": {
